<article id="post-188" class="post-188 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-anomalycon-2014">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://www.anomalycon.com/anomalycon-2014/anomalycon-2015/" rel="bookmark">AnomalyCon 2015</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

				<div class="entry-summary">
				<p>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE<br />
Contact: Kronda Seibert<br />
Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/AnomalyCon<br />
Tumblr: http://anomalycon.tumblr.com/<br />
ANOMALYCON 2015 BRINGS STEAMPUNK SCI-FI/FANTASY TO DENVER TECH CENTER HYATT</p>
			</div><!-- .entry-summary -->
		
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE<br />
Contact: Kronda Seibert<br />
Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/AnomalyCon<br />
Tumblr: http://anomalycon.tumblr.com/<br />
ANOMALYCON 2015 BRINGS STEAMPUNK SCI-FI/FANTASY TO DENVER TECH CENTER HYATT</p>
<p>This year&#8217;s AnomalyCon features the theme &#8220;More Science Than Fiction&#8221;, with specialists on neuroscience, paranormal science, the science of time and MORE! The Geek Rock band The DoubleClicks will be joined by Psyche Corporation, Pandora Celtica, and Keldari Station to explore every nuance of Steampunk all through the night.</p>
<p>Don&#8217;t miss Cory Doctorow, S.J. Chambers, Molly Tanzer, Jason Heller, Mary Anne Mohanraj, Sherri L. Smith, Jody Lynn Nye and dozens more incredible authors as they bring science to life on the page and introduce you to alternate history&#8211;and future&#8211;as you&#8217;ve never experienced it before. Solve a scientifically baffling murder mystery and win fabulous prizes, bring your best costumes for the Grand Costume Contest, participate in our LEGO building or mustache grooming contests, and so much more. AnomalyCon is where Science, Technology, Education and Art Meet.</p>
<p>###</p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

